1
00:01:48,220 --> 00:01:50,900
Why would you come here today?

2
00:01:51,700 --> 00:01:52,980
I want to have a drink

3
00:01:54,180 --> 00:01:54,820
Where's your boyfriend?

4
00:02:04,500 --> 00:02:09,180
Obviously there is something wrong between you

5
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:14,780
I don't understand either

6
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:17,180
What?

7
00:02:20,140 --> 00:02:27,100
If you were in love with someone

8
00:02:28,540 --> 00:02:29,980
Would you marry him?

9
00:02:37,820 --> 00:02:42,260
This is the only treasure my husband gave me before he died

10
00:02:44,140 --> 00:02:45,380
Before he died?

11
00:02:47,740 --> 00:02:50,380
We were very poor when he was alive

12
00:02:51,780 --> 00:02:52,780
It was hard life

13
00:02:55,220 --> 00:02:57,300
He was always drunk returning home

14
00:02:57,740 --> 00:03:00,340
We quarreled every day

15
00:03:02,060 --> 00:03:04,540
Sometimes we even fought

16
00:03:07,020 --> 00:03:08,580
He was really mean to you

17
00:03:11,380 --> 00:03:12,380
I hated him

18
00:03:13,860 --> 00:03:14,900
But I couldn't leave him

19
00:03:17,340 --> 00:03:20,900
We quarreled and fought for so many years

20
00:03:22,780 --> 00:03:23,780
But one day

21
00:03:26,460 --> 00:03:27,620
he's gone

22
00:03:29,180 --> 00:03:31,580
I found he was all I had

23
00:03:39,580 --> 00:03:40,420
I bought this bar

24
00:03:40,580 --> 00:03:42,500
with money he earned by doing three jobs at a time

25
00:03:43,660 --> 00:03:46,620
and insurance money of his car accident

26
00:03:48,900 --> 00:03:51,340
and also the money I earned all these years

27
00:03:56,220 --> 00:04:01,460
He used to promise me that he would run a bar for me

28
00:04:02,940 --> 00:04:04,180
Now the bar is here

29
00:04:06,660 --> 00:04:07,940
But he could never see it

30
00:04:14,340 --> 00:04:14,940
Yezi

31
00:04:15,900 --> 00:04:18,900
I don't know how to answer your question

32
00:04:19,980 --> 00:04:24,700
It always hurts no matter you get married or not

33
00:04:26,100 --> 00:04:30,580
Because we hope that we could be always same as before

34
00:04:31,740 --> 00:04:33,940
Sometimes we keep our promise

35
00:04:34,580 --> 00:04:36,500
Sometimes when we have a quarrel

36
00:04:37,060 --> 00:04:39,340
we shout, 'don't you remember how nice you were to me before?'

37
00:04:40,940 --> 00:04:43,980
We hope the people we love would never change

38
00:04:45,700 --> 00:04:47,740
But when we shout that out

39
00:04:48,860 --> 00:04:52,900
maybe we are the one that have already changed

40
00:05:12,820 --> 00:05:13,340
Come on

41
00:05:24,780 --> 00:05:31,860
[Who are the one that have already changed?]

42
00:05:35,580 --> 00:05:39,580
[Zeyi, I'm kind of under pressure recently. We should stay cool for a while]

43
00:05:49,100 --> 00:05:49,820
Xiang Zeyi

44
00:05:50,340 --> 00:05:52,860
I have heard that you have broken up with Yezi

45
00:05:53,820 --> 00:05:55,220
What's wrong with you?

46
00:05:55,500 --> 00:05:56,980
I have told you

47
00:05:57,540 --> 00:05:59,300
Yezi needs your company

48
00:05:59,460 --> 00:06:00,140
Your company

49
00:06:00,380 --> 00:06:01,620
Don't you understand?

50
00:06:04,380 --> 00:06:05,780
Xiang Zeyi, say something

51
00:06:06,620 --> 00:06:08,660
Xiang Zeyi

52
00:06:32,020 --> 00:06:32,580
Lin Sen

53
00:06:48,020 --> 00:06:48,580
Chen Yiman

54
00:06:50,180 --> 00:06:51,140
I'm here today

55
00:06:52,060 --> 00:06:53,060
to have a talk with you

56
00:07:12,900 --> 00:07:14,060
Actually I love someone else

57
00:07:15,420 --> 00:07:17,260
And I try to forget her

58
00:07:17,620 --> 00:07:18,740
and start a new life

59
00:07:22,500 --> 00:07:24,140
But I found that I failed to deceive myself

60
00:07:27,900 --> 00:07:28,500
I'm sorry

61
00:07:34,380 --> 00:07:35,420
I want to tell you that

62
00:07:36,340 --> 00:07:39,220
I will ask my father to cancel our engagement

63
00:07:40,660 --> 00:07:41,900
I know it's unfair for you

64
00:07:42,500 --> 00:07:43,620
But I hope you could understand

65
00:07:46,020 --> 00:07:46,580
I'm sorry

66
00:08:05,820 --> 00:08:07,340
Finally I can stop acting like a good girl

67
00:08:11,460 --> 00:08:14,620
Actually I got back home on my father's demand

68
00:08:15,740 --> 00:08:16,260
So?

69
00:08:17,140 --> 00:08:18,500
I want to find my boyfriend

70
00:08:19,740 --> 00:08:21,340
and ruin our engagement by the way

71
00:08:22,660 --> 00:08:23,900
so you have already got a boy friend

72
00:08:32,180 --> 00:08:33,380
When I was a child

73
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:35,500
My parents divorced

74
00:08:36,620 --> 00:08:38,100
My father then went on abroad

75
00:08:39,020 --> 00:08:41,420
Mother and I lived a hard life at home

76
00:08:42,580 --> 00:08:44,700
At that time, I usually escaped school

77
00:08:45,620 --> 00:08:47,500
That's how I met my boyfriend

78
00:08:49,220 --> 00:08:51,940
And my parents remarried when I was 16 years old

79
00:08:53,540 --> 00:08:54,980
My father then took me abroad

80
00:08:56,380 --> 00:08:58,460
So I had to be apart from him at that time

81
00:09:02,420 --> 00:09:04,500
Actually I don't like this kind of suit

82
00:09:06,500 --> 00:09:07,980
and symphony

83
00:09:09,180 --> 00:09:11,340
I guess you don't like symphony either, right?

84
00:09:15,220 --> 00:09:16,420
You are a nice guy

85
00:09:16,940 --> 00:09:17,820
I lied to you

86
00:09:18,020 --> 00:09:19,260
But you don't even feel mad at me

87
00:09:25,900 --> 00:09:26,780
Tell me

88
00:09:26,980 --> 00:09:28,420
What's she like?

89
00:09:30,220 --> 00:09:30,740
She

90
00:09:34,020 --> 00:09:36,580
Actually she is a girl with nothing special

91
00:09:38,780 --> 00:09:43,700
But it might be the reason why she is special for me

92
00:09:53,460 --> 00:09:55,460
Why you have bought so many stuffs?

93
00:09:55,980 --> 00:09:56,860
So what?

94
00:09:57,140 --> 00:09:57,900
It's too heavy

95
00:09:58,340 --> 00:09:59,020
How is it possible?

96
00:10:00,020 --> 00:10:01,100
Because it's not you to lift them

97
00:10:01,220 --> 00:10:01,820
It's me

98
00:10:03,060 --> 00:10:03,900
I have to rest for a while

99
00:10:04,380 --> 00:10:05,380
Put them away first

100
00:10:06,100 --> 00:10:06,600
No way

101
00:10:08,100 --> 00:10:08,700
Pardon?

102
00:10:10,020 --> 00:10:10,520
No way

103
00:10:10,980 --> 00:10:11,660
Pardon?

104
00:10:12,460 --> 00:10:13,460
Will you put them away or not?

105
00:10:14,220 --> 00:10:16,100
If you cook stewed pork chops for me this evening

106
00:10:16,260 --> 00:10:17,180
I will do it

107
00:10:17,620 --> 00:10:18,500
It depends

108
00:10:21,780 --> 00:10:22,660
Put this one here

109
00:10:27,740 --> 00:10:28,700
You should

110
00:10:29,140 --> 00:10:31,500
put the fruits and vegetables separately

111
00:10:34,460 --> 00:10:35,140
Who is that?

112
00:10:36,820 --> 00:10:37,660
A friend of mine

113
00:10:38,900 --> 00:10:39,580
A friend?

114
00:10:44,380 --> 00:10:45,540
What did you say just now?

115
00:10:45,780 --> 00:10:48,140
I said, you should put the fruits and vegetables separately

116
00:10:48,300 --> 00:10:48,800
Ok

117
00:10:49,300 --> 00:10:50,260
Put this in the refrigerator first

118
00:10:50,820 --> 00:10:51,780
And later the fruits

119
00:10:58,620 --> 00:11:00,540
Do your work first, ok?

120
00:11:01,500 --> 00:11:02,000
Ok

121
00:11:13,620 --> 00:11:14,260
Anything else?

122
00:11:14,420 --> 00:11:15,180
Look at these

123
00:11:15,380 --> 00:11:17,740
Which one would you like to eat?

124
00:11:17,940 --> 00:11:18,440
This

125
00:11:18,620 --> 00:11:19,120
Ok

126
00:13:53,380 --> 00:13:54,580
Hello, Mr. Yuan

127
00:13:55,060 --> 00:13:56,220
This is Renai Hospital

128
00:13:57,140 --> 00:13:58,900
We have already got your report

129
00:14:00,380 --> 00:14:04,460
The shadow on your brain might be a malignant tumor

130
00:14:04,780 --> 00:14:06,300
Please hurry to the hospital to have a treatment

131
00:14:09,780 --> 00:14:13,220
Doctor, at its worst

132
00:14:14,260 --> 00:14:15,940
how long could I live at most?

133
00:14:17,660 --> 00:14:18,380
Possibly

134
00:14:20,140 --> 00:14:20,860
three months

135
00:14:38,220 --> 00:14:39,540
[Better to drink the yoghurt in three days]

136
00:14:47,940 --> 00:14:50,100
[Remember to have a walk sometimes]

137
00:18:21,340 --> 00:18:22,620
Sorry, I'm late, Mr. Jiang

138
00:18:22,780 --> 00:18:23,420
Have a seat

139
00:18:28,540 --> 00:18:30,540
How do you think of that thing I have mentioned last time?

140
00:18:30,660 --> 00:18:31,160
Thank you

141
00:18:34,220 --> 00:18:36,860
Mr. Jiang, are you sure about that?

142
00:18:39,620 --> 00:18:40,300
if you decide on it

143
00:18:40,300 --> 00:18:41,180
Give me a reply as soon as possible

144
00:18:41,980 --> 00:18:42,480
Ok?

145
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:46,860
Daniao, why are you here?

146
00:18:47,660 --> 00:18:48,540
Why am I here?

147
00:18:49,380 --> 00:18:51,540
Xinrang, tell me who he is

148
00:18:52,260 --> 00:18:53,460
Xinrang, this is

149
00:18:53,660 --> 00:18:55,500
Mr. Jiang, pardon me, let me make an introduction

150
00:18:55,820 --> 00:18:56,420
This is

151
00:18:56,580 --> 00:18:59,580
Liu Xinrang, you are my wife

152
00:18:59,740 --> 00:19:00,780
How could you treat me in this way?

153
00:19:02,700 --> 00:19:03,900
How I treat you?

154
00:19:04,060 --> 00:19:05,180
You wonder how?

155
00:19:05,860 --> 00:19:06,980
Then tell me who he is

156
00:19:08,620 --> 00:19:10,820
Sir, I think there are some misunderstandings

157
00:19:10,980 --> 00:19:11,820
Misunderstandings?

158
00:19:11,980 --> 00:19:12,540
We

159
00:19:12,700 --> 00:19:13,340
Misunderstandings, right?

160
00:19:14,220 --> 00:19:14,860
Misunderstandings

161
00:19:16,020 --> 00:19:16,520
Daniao

162
00:19:16,620 --> 00:19:17,660
It hurts

163
00:19:18,940 --> 00:19:20,020
It hurts

164
00:19:22,420 --> 00:19:23,820
A sculpture studio?

165
00:19:25,100 --> 00:19:26,340
Yeah, that is it

166
00:19:26,540 --> 00:19:29,180
Xinrang wants to raise money for her studio

167
00:19:29,460 --> 00:19:32,420
So she placed some information about the project on crowdfunding website

168
00:19:32,860 --> 00:19:34,980
I'm just an investor on this project

169
00:19:35,500 --> 00:19:36,780
It's a good thing

170
00:19:37,220 --> 00:19:38,860
Xinrang, why didn't you tell me?

171
00:19:40,060 --> 00:19:41,220
Tell you?

172
00:19:41,540 --> 00:19:43,660
You acted like having explosive once you entered

173
00:19:43,900 --> 00:19:44,940
Have you given me any chances to tell you?

174
00:19:45,980 --> 00:19:47,740
But you could tell me before

175
00:19:49,100 --> 00:19:51,940
Before?

176
00:19:53,980 --> 00:19:55,060
Forget it, nothing

177
00:19:56,060 --> 00:19:58,860
Now that we have cleared things up

178
00:19:59,060 --> 00:20:01,100
I shall leave you two alone

179
00:20:01,460 --> 00:20:02,340
I should go now

180
00:20:02,660 --> 00:20:03,700
I'm sorry, Mr. Jiang

181
00:20:03,860 --> 00:20:05,620
Sorry to cause your misunderstanding, Mr. Zhang

182
00:20:05,740 --> 00:20:06,940
Mr. Jiang, thank you trusting me

183
00:20:07,140 --> 00:20:08,020
Nice working with you

184
00:20:08,620 --> 00:20:09,180
Bye

185
00:20:10,820 --> 00:20:11,660
Bye, Mr. Jiang

186
00:20:24,540 --> 00:20:27,460
You know that we aren't young anymore

187
00:20:28,340 --> 00:20:31,100
So it's risky to start a studio

188
00:20:31,900 --> 00:20:33,420
I want to risk it myself

189
00:20:34,380 --> 00:20:36,620
So how would I tell you about it. Alright

190
00:20:37,780 --> 00:20:39,940
Xinrang, I will always support you

191
00:20:40,460 --> 00:20:41,780
no matter what you do

192
00:20:43,140 --> 00:20:44,020
Really?

193
00:20:44,180 --> 00:20:45,180
Of course

194
00:20:45,900 --> 00:20:47,020
Don't you remember?

195
00:20:47,700 --> 00:20:51,780
I have promised to be your own shooting star

196
00:20:52,460 --> 00:20:54,180
and make all your dreams come true

197
00:20:56,900 --> 00:20:58,060
Let's go to have lunch

198
00:20:58,900 --> 00:20:59,420
Go

199
00:21:02,180 --> 00:21:03,700
You should forgive me

200
00:21:04,820 --> 00:21:06,340
Then what will we eat later? Hot pot, ok?

201
00:21:07,180 --> 00:21:08,540
It's all up to you

202
00:21:19,060 --> 00:21:19,560
Hi

203
00:21:23,540 --> 00:21:25,340
It's 2 o'clock p.m. now

204
00:21:26,980 --> 00:21:31,540
I'm glad to live one day longer

205
00:21:35,820 --> 00:21:38,500
I have thought of recording this video for long

206
00:21:39,140 --> 00:21:43,620
But I didn't figure out what I should say

207
00:21:45,660 --> 00:21:48,860
and I'm bad at explaining myself

208
00:21:50,220 --> 00:21:53,380
It always drives Zhuzi mad

209
00:21:57,060 --> 00:22:01,580
So let me start with ordinary opening remarks

210
00:22:04,140 --> 00:22:04,860
To my family

211
00:22:06,340 --> 00:22:06,980
friends

212
00:22:08,180 --> 00:22:11,300
and someone else

213
00:22:13,180 --> 00:22:17,060
When you watch this video

214
00:22:18,620 --> 00:22:19,980
I have already gone

215
00:22:25,500 --> 00:22:28,700
Hold on, I don't mention your name

216
00:22:29,300 --> 00:22:30,660
It's not because you aren't important to me

217
00:22:31,460 --> 00:22:35,460
but because I don't want to make you feel depressed

218
00:22:47,260 --> 00:22:48,420
As a legal examiner

219
00:22:50,340 --> 00:22:55,140
I saw people died every day

220
00:22:56,500 --> 00:22:57,660
But one day

221
00:22:57,860 --> 00:22:59,700
It happens to me

222
00:23:05,100 --> 00:23:06,900
How should I feel?

223
00:23:11,500 --> 00:23:13,020
I don't know either

224
00:23:15,260 --> 00:23:19,220
Maybe it's how people are like

225
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:22,660
We always know too little

226
00:23:26,940 --> 00:23:27,860
No more talking about this

227
00:23:28,540 --> 00:23:29,740
I want to say

228
00:23:31,380 --> 00:23:34,460
Lin Sen, you are my best friend

229
00:23:35,500 --> 00:23:36,740
Stop being silent

230
00:23:39,540 --> 00:23:44,260
No women will want a man that doesn't take any actions

231
00:23:45,260 --> 00:23:46,900
You have loved her for long

232
00:23:47,820 --> 00:23:49,100
So you must get her

233
00:23:49,700 --> 00:23:54,420
Otherwise I will look down on you even on the other side of world

234
00:24:05,940 --> 00:24:06,580
Zhuzi

235
00:24:10,260 --> 00:24:10,940
Darling

236
00:24:12,900 --> 00:24:14,180
After I am gone

237
00:24:15,380 --> 00:24:16,700
you should have meals on time

238
00:24:18,420 --> 00:24:19,620
or it will be bad for your stomach

239
00:24:21,780 --> 00:24:24,660
Find a better man

240
00:24:25,820 --> 00:24:26,900
and marry him

241
00:24:27,820 --> 00:24:33,660
He will be a romantic man unlike me

242
00:24:35,460 --> 00:24:38,340
I sometimes even make you annoyed

243
00:24:43,540 --> 00:24:44,140
Darling

244
00:24:47,660 --> 00:24:52,380
You are tolerant and have devoted a lot to our family

245
00:24:55,260 --> 00:24:56,940
And I am a dull man

246
00:25:15,460 --> 00:25:18,220
Thank you for bring me happiness

247
00:25:19,500 --> 00:25:22,340
which avoids me to be a psycho

248
00:25:24,380 --> 00:25:26,100
Thank you for caring about me

249
00:25:28,940 --> 00:25:32,220
It makes me realize what a life should be like

250
00:25:36,420 --> 00:25:40,420
Actually no one wants to die

251
00:25:44,140 --> 00:25:45,220
Me, either

252
00:25:49,660 --> 00:25:52,060
I remember you used to tell me

253
00:25:55,580 --> 00:25:57,100
People are afraid of death

254
00:25:59,980 --> 00:26:01,740
because they don't want to leave people they love behind

255
00:26:14,900 --> 00:26:15,460
All right

256
00:26:17,540 --> 00:26:20,580
I want to tell you that

257
00:26:21,220 --> 00:26:22,460
You don't need to worry about me

258
00:26:23,940 --> 00:26:25,780
No matter where I am

259
00:26:27,020 --> 00:26:28,100
I will be always watching you

260
00:26:31,900 --> 00:26:33,860
Please take care good of yourselves

261
00:26:42,260 --> 00:26:43,220
I'm your good friend

262
00:26:45,660 --> 00:26:46,780
and Zhuzi's husband

263
00:26:49,420 --> 00:26:50,060
Yuan Lang

264
00:30:11,980 --> 00:30:16,580
Sometimes we think that we are tough enough

265
00:30:17,660 --> 00:30:19,900
always wearing a hard armor

266
00:30:21,420 --> 00:30:25,020
to face all hardships in life bravely

267
00:30:28,180 --> 00:30:29,820
But we seem to forget that

268
00:30:30,460 --> 00:30:34,220
the hard armor is not inherent

269
00:30:35,460 --> 00:30:41,780
but a best gift from our beloved

270
00:30:45,060 --> 00:30:50,300
Maybe we are too accustomed to his or her company

271
00:30:51,380 --> 00:31:02,500
So we will feel at a loss when the company is gone

272
00:31:07,180 --> 00:31:13,980
Happiness we have owned now is just a chance from god

273
00:31:15,380 --> 00:31:18,660
It tells us to fight for it bravely

274
00:31:19,740 --> 00:31:21,100
to defend it cautiously

275
00:31:21,820 --> 00:31:23,500
and to love someone with all your strength

276
00:31:24,780 --> 00:31:26,620
Sometimes though we thought it would last forever

277
00:31:28,340 --> 00:31:30,300
it will be just gone in a sudden
